lelu-shell (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Phase 4b release - first .deb built from the Mavioni/lelu-shell
    fork of linuxmint/Cinnamon.
  * Fork baseline: upstream tag 6.4.6 (commit 52d6af3d7), which matches
    the cinnamon 6.4.6+xia package shipping on Linux Mint 22.1 "Xia".
  * Alongside install: all files land under /opt/lelu-shell/ via
    meson --prefix redirect. Stock cinnamon remains installable and
    defaultable until Phase 6.
  * Single binary package lelu-shell-core ships the binary +
    JavaScript shell tree. Auxiliary Python tools (cinnamon-settings,
    cinnamon-menu-editor, cinnamon-screensaver-lock-dialog,
    cinnamon-desktop-editor) are deliberately omitted - operators use
    stock Mint packages for those until they are ported forward.
  * No Lelu rewrites yet. This is the unchanged-baseline packaging
    that unblocks the Phase 5 per-element rewrite workflow.
  * Documentation: see docs/SHELL-FORK.md in the parent Revenant-OS
    repository for the full fork contract.

 -- Mavioni <massimo.panella625@gmail.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 19:50:00 +0000
